<item>
            <title>[SOCIALFB-18] Boolean results from Facebook cause ClassCastException</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SOCIALFB-18</link>
                <project id="10607" key="SOCIALFB">Spring Social Facebook</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes Facebook returns a &quot;false&quot; when requesting an object. This seems to indicate that the access token does not have sufficient permission to view the requested object (although this should be confirmed). When this happens, a ClassCastException occurs during the binding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The exception thrown is indicative of an internal binding error and should not escape the API boundaries. It should be caught and handled (probably rethrown as some sort of ApiException).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="39110">SOCIALFB-18</key>
            <summary>Boolean results from Facebook cause ClassCastException</summary>
