                            <comment id="69428" author="habuma" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2011 11:47:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed FacebookErrorHandler to interpret any response of &quot;false&quot; as a case of the access token not having sufficient privileges and to throw InsufficientPrivilegeException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Facebook doesn&apos;t document the &quot;false&quot; case anywhere I could find. It is unfortunate that FB uses the vague &quot;false&quot; to indicate what is an error case. Therefore this interpretation is based on testing, observation, and various reports from other developers in forums. If there are other cases where &quot;false&quot; could be returned, we can revisit this and have it throw UncategorizedApiException instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This shouldn&apos;t interfere with normal successful responses from the Graph API, as all Graph API endpoints should either return an object or a collection of objects. From my testing, the only time I could get a boolean value back is when the token doesn&apos;t have sufficient permissions. Even the rare case where an endpoint implies a boolean result (such as the new /&lt;/p&gt;
{user}
&lt;p&gt;/likes/&lt;/p&gt;
{page ID}
&lt;p&gt; endpoint will return either the page data (if the user likes the page) or an empty list (if the user doesn&apos;t like the page) and will not return a boolean.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
